				<div id="post-682" class="hentry p3 post publish author-canuckaholic category-business-tips tag-business tag-essential-apps is-full comments-closed pings-open y2011 m08 d16 h10 slug-10-essential-apps-for-running-your-business"><h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://popdigital.ca/2011/08/16/10-essential-apps-for-running-your-business/" title="Permalink to 10 Essential Apps for Running Your Business" rel="bookmark">10 Essential Apps for Running Your Business</a></h2>
<div class="entry-meta"><span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author">By </span><span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://popdigital.ca/author/admin/" title="View all posts by Adrian">Adrian</a></span><span class="meta-sep meta-sep-entry-date"> | </span><span class="meta-prep meta-prep-entry-date">Published: </span><span class="entry-date"><abbr class="published" title="2011-08-16T17:28:06-0700">August 16, 2011</abbr></span></div><!-- .entry-meta -->
					<div class="entry-content">
<p>The title of the article is actually &#8220;The 10 Essential Apps You Need to Run a Mobile Freelance Business&#8221;, but I think that any business can make use of many of these apps. We already use half of them, and I&#8217;m definitely considering getting the others.</p>
<p><a title="essential apps" href="http://www.sitepoint.com/the-10-essential-apps-you-need-to-run-a-mobile-freelance-business/?utm_medium=email&amp;utm_campaign=Tribune+559+-+Being+Second+to+Market++10+Essential+Mobile+Apps+for+Freelancers+HTML&amp;utm_content=Tribune+559+-+Being+Second+to+Market++10+Essential+Mobile+Apps+for+Freelancers+HTML+CID_8c55f00b05ae341977bbd5ee49ab61e1&amp;utm_source=Newsletter&amp;utm_term=Read+the+rest+of+Joels+article+online" target="_blank">Link</a></p>
<p>The apps are:</p>
<ol>
<li>Paymo</li>
<li>LessAccounting</li>
<li>Gist</li>
<li>HooteSuite</li>
<li>Google Docs</li>
<li>Evernote</li>
<li>Gmail</li>
<li>Skype</li>
<li>Wunderlist</li>
<li>Aviary</li>
</ol>
